- !<Text/de8bb5e5-7619-488d-ae3c-734b88fbc8a0>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: Text
  Enabled: true
  RenderOrder: 999
  StretchMode: Stretch
  VerticalAlignment: Center
  HorizontalAlignment: Left
  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |+
    Navigation Kit Example – Please Read (Part 2)
    
    This example demonstrates how to create a Guided Tour Lens using Custom Locations.
    
    With Custom Locations in Lens Explorer, you can scan a series of real-world locations (small or mid-sized environments) and import the scan data into Lens Studio via code.
    
    Once imported, you can:
    
    Assign a GPS location to each scan
    Add the location to your Place List
    
    What is a Place List?
    
    A Place List is a collection of locations that can include:
    
    GPS-only locations
    Custom Locations linked to GPS coordinates
    
    How the Guided Tour Works
    
    During the guided tour, users can explore locations one by one.
    
    There are two possible behaviors:
    
    1. GPS-Only Locations
       When the user enters the proximity of the GPS location, they receive a notification or alert.
    
    2. Custom Location + GPS
       When the user reaches the GPS proximity, the associated Custom Location activates.
       This allows the Lens to accurately instantiate the virtual content that was previously anchored to that scanned environment.
    
    Tracking Tour Progress
    
    You can monitor the status of the tour through the on-screen status text, which continuously updates to reflect the user’s progress and completion state.
    
