  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    Navigation Kit Example - Please read (Part 1)
    
    This example demonstrates how to create a Navigation Lens with interactive, location-based capabilities.
    
    With this Lens, you can:
    
    Display a map using the built-in Map Component
    
    Detect the user’s position using Navigation GPS
    
    Integrate the Places API to display nearby locations or filter them by category
    
    Select a destination and enable a real-time pointer guiding the user toward it
    
    Optionally retrieve turn-by-turn directions using Mapbox guides (External API)
    
    Create accurate itineraries using Custom Locations
    
    By leveraging Custom Locations, you can improve proximity accuracy around specific GPS coordinates. When a user approaches a point of interest, a Custom Location can be triggered to enhance tracking precision near recognizable mid-size landmarks. This is especially useful for guided tours, allowing visitors to stop directly in front of notable objects or landmarks for an enhanced experience. 
    Getting Started
    
    To start using the example:
    
    Check the Map Component
    In the hierarchy, locate the Map Component and ensure that “Set to Custom Location” is disabled. It should display London as the default location in the editor.
    When you build and run the Lens on your device, your actual location will be displayed automatically.
    
    Use Outdoors for Best Performance
    This Lens performs best outdoors. For accurate north-heading alignment, walk approximately 10–20 meters after launching the experience.
    
    Explore the Navigation Panel
    Use the Navigation Panel to view your current position, adjust zoom levels, apply location filters, and access other navigation controls.
    
    Start Navigation
    Select a location to begin navigating in that direction. The UI will dynamically respond to your movement.
    Once navigation starts, the interface minimizes and splits into two sections to enable hands-free interaction while displaying key navigation information.
    
    
    GPS and HEADING-NORTH works ONLY on device - NOT in Editor
    If you do not find filtered location (Coffee, Restaurant, etc.) chances are there is non categorized as such in your area - if you find places using the "Search Button" (same function but with filter "ALL" - the issue might be related to those filtered buttons and not the Places API.
